      "evidence": [
        "`goseg/docker/orchestration/wireguard.go` has a series of entrypoints (`loadWireguard`, `wgContainerConf`, `buildWgConf`, `writeWgConf`, `WriteWgConfToFile`, `copyWGFileToVolume`) that only delegate to container-layer functions with the same arguments after `wireguardRuntimeFromDocker` conversion.",
        "`goseg/docker/orchestration/container_bridge.go` constructs `container.WireguardRuntime` by direct field assignment from `dockerRuntime` with no transformation or invariant enforcement.",
        "`goseg/docker/orchestration/runtime_seams.go` default adapters (`runtimeContainerAdapter`, `runtimeUrbitAdapter`, `runtimeConfigAdapter`, etc.) mainly forward to concrete funcs (`StartContainer`, `GetLatestContainerInfo`, etc.) rather than adding abstraction behavior."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Collapse the wireguard orchestration seam into one seam boundary: either keep orchestration->runtime conversion in a single package boundary and expose only operation-level methods with real policy, or remove redundant forwarding layers where they only wrap/call-through. This reduces chain depth and makes dependency direction clearer for debugging and testing.",
