      "evidence": [
        "`goseg/defaults/defaults.go` defines a full `WgConfig` struct with concrete defaults (`WireguardVersion`, `Repo`, hashes, `CapAdd`, `Sysctls`, `Volumes`).",
        "`goseg/config/wireguardbuilder/builder.go` reconstructs a `structs.WgConfig` manually and re-embeds similar default fields (`WireguardName`, `CapAdd`, `Volumes`, `Sysctls`) with only a few version-driven fields changed.",
        "Because these are manually repeated, updates to one default definition do not automatically flow to the builder, making behavior divergence possible across codepaths."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Introduce a single canonical Wireguard default source and have `BuildConfig` derive all static defaults from it (then override only the version-dependent fields). Add a narrow builder that cannot drift from `defaults.WgConfig` unless explicitly changed.",
